# CLAWT Project Overview

CLAWT is a **verifiable AI agent platform on EigenCompute**. Users sign in with Ethereum wallets (MetaMask + SIWE), deploy personal AI agents into Trusted Execution Environments (TEEs), and submit natural-language tasks. Every agent response is cryptographically signed by the agent's TEE wallet.

## Architecture

```
Frontend (Vercel)  →  Backend (VPS)  →  Agent (EigenCompute TEE)
   Next.js 16           Express           Express + LLM loop
   React 19             SQLite            HD Wallet (viem)
   ethers v6            ecloud CLI        Skill execution
```

## Workspace Layout

```
ClawT/
├── agent/       # TEE agent (Docker, runs on EigenCompute)
├── backend/     # Orchestration API (runs on VPS)
├── frontend/    # Web UI (deployed to Vercel)
├── nginx/       # Reverse proxy config
└── package.json # npm workspaces root
```

## Deployment URLs

- **Backend API**: `http://<VPS_IP>` (nginx proxy to port 4000)
- **Frontend**: Vercel (has SSO protection - use Vercel MCP `get_access_to_vercel_url` for shareable links)
- **VPS code path**: `/opt/clawt/`
- **PM2 process**: `clawt-backend`

## Key Technologies

| Layer | Stack |
|-------|-------|
| Frontend | Next.js 16, React 19, Tailwind v4, ethers v6, siwe v3 |
| Backend | Express, better-sqlite3, siwe v2, viem, zod, @scure/bip39 |
| Agent | Express, viem (wallet), gray-matter (skills), EigenAI API |
| Runtime | Node 20, TypeScript strict, ESM, tsx (no build step) |

## Auth Flow

1. Frontend requests nonce from `/api/auth/nonce`
2. User signs SIWE message with MetaMask
3. Backend verifies signature, returns HMAC-SHA256 session token (24h TTL)
4. All requests use `Authorization: Bearer <token>`

## Important Conventions

- Project name is **CLAWT** everywhere (not SkillsSeal)
- One agent per user (enforced at deploy)
- Agent mnemonic generated at deploy time, injected as env var, never stored in DB
- All agent responses are signed by the TEE wallet
- Use Foundry for Solidity (not Hardhat)
